# Dotfiles Repository Rules

Read and follow the guidelines in AGENTS.md at the repository root. It contains:
- Architecture rules (directory structure, POSIX sh requirements, XDG compliance)
- Neovim config conventions (lazy.nvim specs, keymap namespaces, how to add plugins/LSP servers)
- Bash config conventions (fragment files, load order)
- Documentation requirements (keep cheatsheets in docs/ in sync with any changes)

Key points to always remember:
- Shell scripts use POSIX sh (#!/bin/sh), not bash — except files under home/bash/
- All scripts must be idempotent
- Interactive reads use /dev/tty
- Never commit secrets
- When changing keymaps or configs, update the matching cheatsheet in docs/
